# Project Contract

- Keep scope minimal and aligned with the lightweight MVP.
- Do not overengineer MVP features.
- Prefer simple, readable, production-safe code.
- Do not introduce broad refactors unless explicitly requested.
- Preserve current user-facing behavior unless explicitly requested.
- Keep user-facing UI in Russian unless explicitly requested otherwise.
- For risky tasks, start with audit/plan mode before implementation.
- Always summarize changed files and provide a commit message.
